negotiator.protocol

Class MultilateralProtocolAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • negotiator.protocol.MultilateralProtocolAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultilateralProtocol
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AlternatingOfferConsensusProtocol, AlternatingOfferMajorityVotingProtocol, MediatorProtocol, StackedAlternatingOffersProtocol

    public abstract class MultilateralProtocolAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements MultilateralProtocol
    An adapter for the protocol class. This will implement all the methods int the Protocol interface and return default values for them.
    Author:
    David Festen

      • isFinished

        public boolean isFinished(Session session,
                 java.util.List<NegotiationPartyInternal> parties)
        Check if the protocol is done or still busy. If this method returns true, the SessionManager will not start a new .Round after the current one. It will however finish all the turns described in the getRoundStructure(java.util.List, negotiator.session.Session) method.
        Specified by:
        isFinished in interface MultilateralProtocol
        Parameters:
        session - the current state of this session
        Returns:
        true if the protocol is finished

        getActionListeners in interface MultilateralProtocol

      • getCurrentAgreement

        public Bid getCurrentAgreement(Session session,
                      java.util.List<NegotiationPartyInternal> parties)
        This method should return the current agreement.

        Some protocols only have an agreement at the negotiation session, make sure that this method returns null until the end of the session in that case, because this method might be queried at intermediary steps.

        Specified by:
        getCurrentAgreement in interface MultilateralProtocol
        Parameters:
        session - The complete session history up to this point
        parties - The parties involved in the current negotiation
        Returns:
        The agreed upon bid or null if no agreement
